# Product Requirements Document (PRD)
## Feature: SHIDEK Self-Improving AI Assistant

**Product:** SHIDEK 2.0 — Career & College AI (Gujarat NEET/GUJCET counseling)
**Doc owner:** [Shivam Soni]
**Status:** Draft v1

---

### 1. Background

SHIDEK currently helps Gujarat NEET/GUJCET students with rank prediction, college search,
comparisons, scholarships, and an AI chat tool. Users have reported frequent wrong/irrelevant
answers from the AI chat. This PRD defines a feature to make SHIDEK's answers improve over
time by learning from real conversations, while keeping student data private.

### 2. Problem Statement

- The AI chat gives inconsistent or incorrect answers (cutoffs, dates, rules change yearly and
  the model has no Gujarat-specific memory).
- There is no mechanism today to capture "this answer was wrong" feedback and act on it.
- Any improvement that calls multiple AI providers must not leak a student's name, NEET roll
  number, score, phone, or any personal identifier to those providers or to other students.

### 3. Goals

1. SHIDEK's chat answers measurably improve over time using real usage data.
2. The system can consult one or more external AI providers (Gemini, ChatGPT, Perplexity,
   Claude) to cross-check or enrich an answer, without exposing API keys or personal data.
3. Every student-identifying field is stripped or anonymized before any data leaves the
   student's own session.
4. Admin (Shivam) can review what the assistant is learning and correct bad entries.

### 4. Non-Goals (explicitly out of scope)

- This is **not** retraining or fine-tuning an AI model. No SHIDEK feature will alter the
  weights of Gemini/ChatGPT/Claude/Perplexity — that is not possible from a client app, and
  not necessary to achieve the goal.
- This is not a guarantee of 100% accurate answers — admission rules and cutoffs change yearly
  and always need a verified-source disclaimer.

### 5. User Stories

| As a... | I want to... | So that... |
|---|---|---|
| Student | Ask SHIDEK a question and get a confident, correct answer | I can trust it for admission decisions |
| Student | Flag an answer as wrong/unhelpful | Future users don't get the same bad answer |
| Admin | See which questions SHIDEK answers badly | I can fix the knowledge base directly |
| Admin | Approve/reject auto-learned facts before they go live | Wrong info never gets "learned" permanently |
| Any user | Trust that my name/score/phone is never sent to a 3rd-party AI | My privacy is protected |

### 6. Functional Requirements

**FR1 — Feedback capture**
Every AI chat answer has 👍/👎 buttons. 👎 prompts an optional 1-line reason.

**FR2 — Anonymization before any external call**
Before a question is sent to any AI provider, the app strips: name, phone, email, NEET roll
number, exact score (rounded to nearest 10), category, and any free-text the user typed that
matches PII patterns (regex-based redaction client-side, enforced again server-side).

**FR3 — Multi-AI consult (server-side only)**
A backend function (not the browser) may call one or more of Gemini / OpenAI / Perplexity /
Claude APIs server-side, using server-held secret keys, to answer or verify a question. The
browser never sees any API key.

**FR4 — Growing knowledge base**
Anonymized Q&A pairs with positive feedback are stored in a knowledge base (KB). Future
questions first search the KB (cheap, fast, no external call needed) before calling any AI
provider — this is the actual "learning" mechanism: a constantly improving FAQ/answer index,
not model retraining.

**FR5 — Admin review queue**
New KB entries sit in "pending" status until Shivam approves them in a simple admin view.
Approved entries become searchable; rejected entries are deleted.

**FR6 — Source-of-truth override**
Official cutoffs/dates/rules (ACPC, GUJCET, NEET) entered manually by admin always outrank
AI-generated answers on the same topic.

**FR7 — Transparency**
Chat UI shows a small label "🔎 Verified" (KB-sourced) vs "🤖 AI-suggested" (model-generated,
unverified) so students know how reliable an answer is.

### 7. Success Metrics

- ↓ 👎 rate on AI chat answers, month over month.
- ↑ % of answers served from KB (cheaper, faster, more reliable) vs raw AI call.
- 0 incidents of personal data sent to a 3rd-party AI provider (tracked via server logs).
- Admin review queue cleared within 48h on average.

### 8. Risks / Open Questions

- Need API keys/budget for any external AI provider used server-side — cost must be capped.
- Need to decide where the backend lives (current app is 100% static GitHub Pages with no
  server) — see Technical Architecture doc.
- Legal/ToS: each AI provider has its own terms for automated/API use; review before wiring up
  any specific provider.
